reviews.text: They original Cova in Milan is an Icon of that city, both for food and service quality. Here the shopping mall placement of this restaurant is not very nice, they should try to have a better location, the food and service are ok, but they don't justify the price level.

Revisited this place last Saturday. Brunch was offered with an attractive price. Choice of dessert was surprisingly plenty and the quality was very good. Nice place for a Saturday brunch if you are near harbour city
good food and good service
Store bought pastries and watery coffee, costing HKD 500 for two persons. Presentation lacks elegance. A shameful representation of Cova or Milanese style dining.

Have been here before for tea and cake. A major disappointment this afternoon. Very poor service. The waitress didn't show any interest or enthusiasm, did not give us the menu for afternoon tea set, and replied dismissively and somewhat condescendingly in Cantonese when we spoke to her in English. The cakes were half melt with their cream, and so was the decorative side cream. Not acceptable for what is supposed to be a high end caffe in a prime shopping/tourist district.

reviews.text: Good arcade to shop for medium to medium-high end brands in a spacious environment with both restaurants and food court to suit varying tastes of customers. Great parking lot. Multiple sakes receipts accepted for free parking.

Very crowded and very clean like a hospital. Come here on Sunday and you can enjoy waiting for a table for an hour with everyone. Best place if you want to buy a Rolex for $900,000 to go with your yacht sitting in a port in Italy.
Multiple restaurants and shops. A very big mall, and a nice theater to watch movies. The restaurants were also very nice. A very good shopping mall overall.

I like Festival Walk as it is rarely super crowded like the malls at Sha Tin always seem to be. The TASTE supermarket is fantastic here with a range of products from around the world including Waitrose products and a good frozen section. Other stores I like here are Zara Home, Log On, M&S and the Cinema which let's you bring Starbucks in. I sometimes come here to walk around on rainy days too as it is so big and there are very few shoppers with suitcases.

I like Windows shopping here.cause if not people mountain people sea. Can very relaxed to take a look.some shop I used take a look.like hk a female designer.
